commit.message:
Use "curses" as dependency to work on OpenBSD and everywhere

On OpenBSD "ncurses" is named "curses" so the old dependency didn't work
there. Meson wraps curses and ncurses into the "curses" dependency with
preference on ncurses. Perfect!

commit.message:
os.h: Fix includes on musl

sysctl.h is only officially present in <linux/sysctl.h>, not
<sys/sysctl.h>.
Add alpine / OpenBSD to the README
Update README and fix theme installation
Add install steps to meson.build
Add meson build file

Remove FDDI media detection

FreeBSD 12 removed support for FDDI (and Token Ring). As FDDI and
Token Ring are extinct nowadays we don't nee to support this.

Signed-off-by: Matthias Schmitz <matthias@sigxcpu.org>
fix man page documentation for -d

Remove the confusing use of BUFSIZE

Reading BUFSIZ-1 chars (8091) into a BUFSIZE'd buffer (256) is dangerous.

Now only the macro BUFSIZ is used.

Thanks to @prspkt and @sauyon for pointing this out earlier.

Remove deprecated <sys/sysctl.h> from Linux build

As already reported by Sam James (@thesamesam) and in the Debian
bugtracker #993874 the <sys/sysctl.h> is deprecated since a while.

Update and rename README to README.md

So that it actually show as markdown and not raw code
Travis-ci:added support for ppc64le
